Equine piroplasmosis, Ecuador
-----------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 7 Aug 2015 from Dr Diego Alfonso Viscaino Cabezas, [agricultural engineer, Ministry of Agriculture, Livestock, Aquaculture and Fisheries], Quito, Ecuador

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 26 Jun 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 31 Jul 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 1996
Causal agent: _Babesia caballi_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks: 1
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (1075): Guayas, Chongon, Guayaquil, Guayas
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Jun 2015
Outbreak status: resolved (7 Aug 2015)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 98 / 38 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: adult equine males and females for recreation.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 39 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.
Epidemiological comments: this event has been notified by the [person(s)] responsible for the holding dedicated to equine for recreation. During monitoring activities, serological surveillance of all susceptible species having been in contact [with the affected horses] was undertaken.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; disinfection/disinfestation; control of vectors; dipping/spraying; no vaccination; treatment of affected animals (anti-parasite treatment)
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Animal Health AGROCALIDAD (national laboratory) / Equidae / competitive ELISA (c-ELISA) 31 Jul 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

